The Hook System is the plugin's extensibility backbone, providing a 52–59 hook lifecycle management system (depending on whether Team Mode is enabled) that intercepts and modifies behavior at critical execution points. Hooks enable features like auto-context injection, error recovery, model fallback, and task continuation enforcement without modifying core OpenCode logic.

For information about creating plugin components (agents, tools, commands), see [Plugin System](/code-yeongyu/oh-my-openagent/2.1-plugin-system). For details on how hooks integrate with the configuration system, see [Configuration Pipeline](/code-yeongyu/oh-my-openagent/2.4-configuration-pipeline).

